<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-01-02T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-01-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="682" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/334a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kaufman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-02T16:00:00-05:00">January 2, 1929—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>2. Department’s January 2, 11 a.m. Conference will hold a plenary
                                session on Friday<note n="11" xml:id="d682fn11">January 4.</note>
                                morning at eleven o’clock and it is hoped that protocol may be
                                signed before that time. The Conference will probably adjourn on
                                Saturday.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>